00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:48.000
Bel Ami, presented at the Berlin Film Festival, has really surprised the audience.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:53.000
Directed by Declan Donnellan together with Nick Ormerod, and written by Rachel Bennette,

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:58.000
the film is yet another adaptation from the novel by French writer Guy de Maupassant.

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:02.000
It’s the story of George Duroy, played by Robert Pattinson,

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:06.000
a young libertine journalist who, driven by his ambition,
0:01:06.000,0:00:12.000
scandalizes the Parisian high society making his way through thanks to his sex appeal.

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:17.000
Alongside with the young Pattison, there is Christina Ricci in the role of Clotilde,

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:21.000
a young housewife who begins an erotic relationship with the main character.

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:24.000
Also starring Kristin Scott Thomas and Uma Thurman,

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:49.000
Speaking of Uma Thurman, she’ll be the special guest in five episodes

00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:55.000
of the first season of "Smash", which airs in the U.S. since January the 6th.

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:57.000
The TV series, produced by Steven Spielberg,

00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:00.000
tells the story of a Broadway company attempting

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:03.000
to create a musical about the life of Marilyn Monroe.

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:06.000
Thurman will play an actress in need,

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:08.000
willing to do anything to grab the role of Marilyn.

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:11.000
That's all for today.

